<anchor xml:id="_namespace_sabre_1_1_event_1_1_promise_1a1a337f08ad199faf88c585d6d7ad13d8"/><section>
    <title>all()</title>
<indexterm><primary>all</primary><secondary>Sabre\Event\Promise</secondary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>Sabre\Event\Promise</primary><secondary>all</secondary></indexterm>
<para><computeroutput>all (array $promises)</computeroutput></para>
<para>This file contains a set of functions that are useful for dealing with the Promise object.</para>

<para><formalpara><title>Copyright</title>

<para>Copyright (C) fruux GmbH (<link xlink:href="https://fruux.com/">https://fruux.com/</link>) </para>
</formalpara>
<formalpara><title>Auteur</title>

<para>Evert Pot (<link xlink:href="http://evertpot.com/">http://evertpot.com/</link>) @license <link xlink:href="http://sabre.io/license/">http://sabre.io/license/</link> Modified BSD License This function takes an array of Promises, and returns a Promise that resolves when all the given arguments have resolved.</para>
</formalpara>
The returned Promise will resolve with a value that&apos;s an array of all the values the given promises have been resolved with.</para>

<para>This array will be in the exact same order as the array of input promises.</para>

<para>If any of the given Promises fails, the returned promise will immediately fail with the first Promise that fails, and its reason.</para>

